This paper is about joint extraction of entities and relations, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new model structure and a multi-task learning framework equipped with copy mechanism to improve the accuracy of entity extraction and enable the prediction of multi-token entities. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related tasks. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these sub-categories also cover topics related to NLP and machine learning.
